{"TopicId":53144,"ForumId":16,"TopicTitle":"How hard can a Kerbal hold on?","CreatedByName":"Lar-E","CreatedById":78160,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-14T23:24:10Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"Lar-E","CreatedById":78160,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-14T23:24:10Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Ei.e. to a ladder rung or such, in terms of acceleration?\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Jason Patterson","CreatedById":44388,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-15T00:03:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003ENot very. If you build a rover with a flat top and place a kerbal on top hanging onto a ladder, it will slide around pretty freely as you speed up/slow down. They appear to be able to resist infinite sideways forces though.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TechnicalK3rbal","CreatedById":86903,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-15T00:14:16Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EI think it\u0027s approximately 5 g\u0027s.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Galacticruler","CreatedById":58398,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-15T00:18:57Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003Evertically, 5 Gs, horozontally?\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:18px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-family:\u0027Comic Sans MS\u0027;\u0022\u003E\u00C3\u00A2\u00CB\u2020\u00C5\u00BE\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"TechnicalK3rbal","CreatedById":86903,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-15T01:08:29Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E5 Gs parallels to the plane of the ladder.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wronkiew","CreatedById":60802,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-15T07:59:14Z","Content":"\n\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://www.wronkiewicz.net/images/ksp_jeb_hold_on.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022ksp_jeb_hold_on.jpg\u0022\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Geoff-AU","CreatedById":91720,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-16T09:25:46Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E^^ yeah last time I tried that my Kerbal became a secondary fireball.. needless to say it didn\u0027t end well.\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"wronkiew","CreatedById":60802,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-11-17T04:44:05Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003EOh, they landed it. Took some finagling to keep Jeb on the ladder.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cimg src=\u0022http://www.wronkiewicz.net/images/ksp_jeb_splash.jpg\u0022 alt=\u0022ksp_jeb_splash.jpg\u0022\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EQuite an EVA report!\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}